					<description><![CDATA[Click here for the other sessions. Side Expedition 2U 06 Feb 2026 Adventurers: On their return to the sunken hut, the party found some fresh footprints wandering about and then leading inland. Wary of another party of humans potentially at their backs, they splashed into the dungeon. With the main entrance chamber unoccupied, the group &#8230; <a href="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/02/16/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-157/" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="screen-reader-text">The Keep on Yeoldelands &#8211; Session&#160;157</span></a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em><strong><a href="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/keep-on-yeoldelands/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Click here for the other sessions.</a> </strong></em></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Side Expedition 2U</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em>06 Feb 2026</em></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Adventurers</strong>:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Elixabete (Dwarf 4)</li>



<li>Firstleaf (Elf 2)</li>



<li>Groucho (Fighter 2)</li>



<li>Hartely (Bard 2)</li>



<li>Maistlyn (Magic User 2)</li>



<li>Mike (Cleric 4)</li>



<li>Assorted NPCs: Artizar (F1), Atze (T1), Ecclesdale (F1), Mendoria (MU1), Mitxel (F1), Negu (H2)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">On their return to the sunken hut, the party found some fresh footprints wandering about and then leading inland. Wary of another party of humans potentially at their backs, they splashed into the dungeon. With the main entrance chamber unoccupied, the group opted against further exploration through the secret door they’d discovered last time and instead headed for a door they’d seen down one corridor.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Raising their cloaks to their noses in a mild attempt to ward away the stench, they opened the door into a makeshift latrine. There was another door across the room, crudely-barricaded with a warning painted across it in a warped form of halflingo. Nobody was willing to wade over to investigate, so they sent Firstleaf over to have a look through it with his leather armour of ethereability.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">On the other side of the door was a small room populated only by a swankily-dressed body pinned to the wall by a softly glowing sword. To the elf’s surprise, the figure raised his head and greeted the incorporeal interloper with a sharp-toothed grin. The unabashed vampire was all obsequious politeness, and requested aid in escaping in return for a solemn promise to not do them any harm and information on the Cardinal, the fellow in charge of this underground complex. Firstleaf promised to think about it, returned to fill in the rest of the party and, following precedent, they decided to leave for their future selves to deal with. The glowing sword might come in useful, after all.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<figure data-carousel-extra='{&quot;blog_id&quot;:173068755,&quot;permalink&quot;:&quot;https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/02/16/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-157/&quot;}'  class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="743" data-attachment-id="5622" data-permalink="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/02/16/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-157/2026-02-05/" data-orig-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png" data-orig-size="3504,2544" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="2026.02.05" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=656" data-id="5622" src="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-5622" srcset="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=1024 1024w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=2048 2048w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=150 150w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=300 300w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=768 768w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026.02.05.png?w=1440 1440w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
</figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Further exploration brought them to the sounds of multiple Angry Wee Fellows and, preferring not to leave so boisterous an enemy along any potential escape route, they charged in and attacked. Unfortunately, their attempt to burst through was once again hampered by an obstinate door, so the Awfs had enough warning to scramble behind some spiky barricades made of swords and wood.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The close-quarter-focused adventurers assaulted these defences while their ranged companions tried flinging spells and missiles from the doorway. Alas, Mendoria’s magical lullaby only affected one of them, and the little balls of hyperactive rage proved stiff resistance. For all his armour, Groucho was nearly cut down by an oversized sword and was forced to stagger back and receive a hasty prayer from Brother Mike.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The awfs fought violently to the last, but eventually party’s Magic Missiles, regular missiles, flaming oil and accumulated arsenal of enchanted weapons overcame their dozen foes. Just one remained, blinded by a Light spell and wrestled to the ground by four adventurers.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As soon as the party mentioned that they were here to deal fight the Kozengi, or whatever these “watery gits” were calling themselves, the captive was all to happy to cooperate, spewing forth his contempt for the three-eyed foe and proudly boasting of his duty to protect the “massive egg”. With his aggression seemingly diverted elsewhere, the party released him to convey their own feelings to the rest of his kind while they, bloodied after the fight, returned to Fourtowers Bridge to lick their wounds and make plans.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">GM Notes</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>It has been wryly noted that we’ve come across a number of latrines and imprisoned immortals in these ‘side’ expeditions. While this is just the coincidence of two modules happening to have examples of each, it’s worth making a note that I may need to modify some of these features should they crop up in other modules. I don’t think they’re especially prevalent tropes in old school modules, but no harm in being mindful of avoidable patterns.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>
