		<category><![CDATA[Yeoldelands]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/?p=5573</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Click here for the other sessions. Side Expedition 2S 22 Jan 2026 Adventurers: After some overhead scouting astride the nearly fully grown griffons failed to reveal an immediately obvious hideout for the ambushing brigands in the woods, the party decided to explore a little way downriver, particularly interested in an old, partially submerged hut built &#8230; <a href="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/27/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-154/" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="screen-reader-text">The Keep on Yeoldelands &#8211; Session&#160;154</span></a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em><strong><a href="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/keep-on-yeoldelands/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Click here for the other sessions.</a> </strong></em></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Side Expedition 2S</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em>22 Jan 2026</em></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Adventurers</strong>:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Elixabete (Dwarf 4)</li>



<li>Groucho (Fighter 1)</li>



<li>Hartley (Bard 1)</li>



<li>Mike (Cleric 4)</li>



<li>Assorted NPCs: Artizar (F1), Atze (T1), Ecclesdale (F1), Mitxel (F1), Negu (H2),</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After some overhead scouting astride the nearly fully grown griffons failed to reveal an immediately obvious hideout for the ambushing brigands in the woods, the party decided to explore a little way downriver, particularly interested in an old, partially submerged hut built into the cliffs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Sploshing around the doorway revealed some swords underwater, all made out of different, bizarre materials such as leather and deteriorating rat corpses, reminding the adventurers of the peculiar blades they’d found on the Angry Wee Fellows in the copper mine. Warily, they advanced along a tunnel into the cliff, finding and triggering a trap which set off some form of alarm.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After waiting to see if anyone would come, they continued on to find half a dozen of the diminutive humanoids having a competitive punch up while they waited for the intruders. Negu tried translating the party’s various attempts to look threatening while promising peace. Confused, the least small awf asked for clarity. When the adventurers assured peace, the wild-haired green scrappers rolled their eyes, exclaimed, “Boring!” and charged.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The adventurers ran forward to meet them and bring their numbers and size to bear, and the awfs were cut down without loss, fighting aggressively to the last.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The party went about healing their wounded and sent Atze, their newly hired thief, to climb up a great statue depicting a three-eyed Kozengi warrior and start prying out a particularly shiny and expensive-looking central eye. As she did so, the others extracted two softly glowing swords from a pile.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Mitxel gave a whispered warning: he’d spied another pile of swords approaching, seemingly hovering in the air, from one of the corridors leading out. The adventurers hid behind some pillars and doused their light sources. By the faint glow from the two weapons they’d found, they saw the other gathered swords slowly approach them.#</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<figure data-carousel-extra='{&quot;blog_id&quot;:173068755,&quot;permalink&quot;:&quot;https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/27/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-154/&quot;}'  class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-10 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="670" data-attachment-id="5575" data-permalink="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/27/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-154/2026-01-22/" data-orig-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png" data-orig-size="1859,1218" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="2026.01.22" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png?w=656" data-id="5575" src="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-5575" srcset="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png?w=1024 1024w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png?w=150 150w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png?w=300 300w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png?w=768 768w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png?w=1440 1440w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.22.png 1859w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
</figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As it disappeared around one pillar, Mike felt a burning pain as something moist and gloopy eased up his sleeve. Shaking life back into it, he struck his magical torch alight and saw more clearly now a gelatinous mass looming over him. He and Ecclesdale scrambled back, and the party launched their entire arsenal of oil flasks at the oozing cube.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After it had fizzled into nothing, they packed away the glowing swords and splashed out the ruined hut back to safety, eager to find a buyer for Atze’s sizeable gem.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">GM Notes</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Having discussed bandit hunting throughout the week running up to this session, the players decided to volte face and opted to explore the little hut that had been on the map for the last year or so. This is where the easy-to-read dungeon come into their own; I’d read this module a while ago, but definitely needed to refresh my memory while the players pondered their equipment stocks. Succinct, characterful room keys are a GM’s best friend.</li>



<li>Nearly got Mike with the near-invisible gelatinous cube. Could almost hear the slaps to the forehead as the more experienced players finally realised what was in front of them.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
