		<category><![CDATA[Session Report]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Yeoldelands]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/?p=5544</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Click here for the other sessions. Side Expedition 2Q 06 Jan 2026 Adventurers: The villagers had heard enough tales of the gatehouse to refuse any prospect of spending too much time within it, and it seemed anyone signing up for the task would want a cut of the profits, so the adventurers decided to carry &#8230; <a href="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/11/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-152/" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="screen-reader-text">The Keep on Yeoldelands &#8211; Session&#160;152</span></a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em><strong><a href="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/keep-on-yeoldelands/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Click here for the other sessions.</a> </strong></em></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Side Expedition 2Q</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em>06 Jan 2026</em></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Adventurers</strong>:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Edward (Cleric 3)</li>



<li>Elixabete (Dwarf 4)</li>



<li>Firstleaf (Elf 2)</li>



<li>Groucho (Fighter 1)</li>



<li>Hartley (Bard 1)</li>



<li>Mike (Cleric 4)</li>



<li>Assorted NPCs: Ecclesdale (F1), Flintoffden (MU1), Mendoria (MU1), Mitxel (F1), Negu (H2),</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The villagers had heard enough tales of the gatehouse to refuse any prospect of spending too much time within it, and it seemed anyone signing up for the task would want a cut of the profits, so the adventurers decided to carry out the collapsed temple excavation project themselves.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The initial excursion took them down to the copper mine to see what serviceable tools remained, stopping by to see how the chained, flaming skeleton was doing. Still in agony, it seemed, and spotting the magical gems hanging around several party members’ necks he begged them to release him. More immersed in the ways of Holy Harold now, Mike channelled his divine vision to determine that the skeleton was of a decidedly chaotic nature. Assuring him that would definitely be back, the party withdrew to ponder the significance of this, taking a number of shovels and pickaxes with them.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It turned out that the cave affected pretty much the entirety of the Snake-Armed Goddess’ temple area. Firstleaf went in with the armour of ethereability to confirm the extent of the collapse, and found the four-armed stone guardian wedged under some rubble but still active.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<figure data-carousel-extra='{&quot;blog_id&quot;:173068755,&quot;permalink&quot;:&quot;https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/11/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-152/&quot;}'  class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-14 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="625" data-attachment-id="5547" data-permalink="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/11/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-152/2026-01-06/" data-orig-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png" data-orig-size="1542,942" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="2026.01.06" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png?w=656" data-id="5547" src="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-5547" srcset="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png?w=1024 1024w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png?w=150 150w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png?w=300 300w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png?w=768 768w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png?w=1440 1440w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026.01.06.png 1542w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
</figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The party returned to the village for supplies of lamp oil and food, and working their way through the fallen stone under Elixabete’s dwarven guidance. They worked in shifts, half the band mining, shifting rubble or guarding at any one time while the rest did what they could to get some rest in the level above, avoiding the torture chambers and cells for the more habitable rooms.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Other than the occasional sound of something moving on the other side of the spiked door, which the guards had no desire to investigate, the adventurers were able to work this way for a full two days, crafting a path through to the room full of holy symbols they’d seen during their first descent. Holy Harold’s blessing, through Mike, ensured they could work their way through the room untroubled, and eventually they gathered up a pile of amulets of various designs and materials.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Believing there to be more treasure down here, especially beyond the trapped stone statue, the party decided to return to the village for the time being to see some daylight again and look for some passing merchants with an interest in religious iconography.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">GM Notes</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>I don’t know the next thing about mining and excavating, so I’m sure the timings we worked out for the party to work their way through the cave in were well below a realistic estimate. Rather than bog the game down, though, I went for something gameable: two hours to work through a 5’ square, assuming two characters doing the digging and two clearing the rubble. We could work that out on the map nice and quickly, players could make decisions as to which way they wanted to go and when, and the remarkably efficient progress could be handwaved as being down to having a dwarf in charge.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
