					<description><![CDATA[Click here for the other sessions. Side Expedition 2P 11 Dec 2025 Adventurers: The band of adventurers returned to the gatehouse, making their way back down to the copper mine level to pick up their metallic construct to weaponise against Contithius, the Snake-Armed Goddess’ guardian with a charming hold over the hairy ones. Unfortunately, the &#8230; <a href="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/06/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-150-2/" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="screen-reader-text">The Keep on Yeoldelands &#8211; Session&#160;151</span></a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em><strong><a href="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/keep-on-yeoldelands/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Click here for the other sessions.</a> </strong></em></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Side Expedition 2P</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em>11 Dec 2025</em></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Adventurers</strong>:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Carbel (Halfling 4)</li>



<li>Edward (Cleric 2)</li>



<li>Elixabete (Dwarf 4)</li>



<li>Mike (Cleric 4)</li>



<li>Assorted NPCs: Ecclesdale (F1), Flintoffden (MU1), Koldobike (E1), Negu (H2)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The band of adventurers returned to the gatehouse, making their way back down to the copper mine level to pick up their metallic construct to weaponise against Contithius, the Snake-Armed Goddess’ guardian with a charming hold over the hairy ones. Unfortunately, the found Metal Mickey in pieces and surrounded by several corpses of the little humanoid bundles of rage they’d encountered on previous expeditions. The rope the construct had been guarding had also been cut from the bottom, and there was no sign of the raft it had been securing.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After fighting their way through a roaming band of live little angry humanoids, the party headed for the Snake-Armed Goddess’ temple. They quickly and silently cut down several snake and hairy guards, rescuing a pair of kidnapped caravan guards and convincing them to aid in the upcoming battle.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Unfortunately their lowered shoulders were once again insufficient to bash down the door to the temple quickly enough to seize the element of surprise, and so the goddess’ disciples were ready for the party’s assault. Missiles flew and destroyed what turned out to be Contithius’ mirrored images, and both sides exchanged sleep-inducing spells, sending the majority of the combatants into an enchanted doze.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<figure data-carousel-extra='{&quot;blog_id&quot;:173068755,&quot;permalink&quot;:&quot;https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/06/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-150-2/&quot;}'  class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-15 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="589" data-attachment-id="5534" data-permalink="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/2026/01/06/the-keep-on-yeoldelands-session-150-2/2025-12-11/" data-orig-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png" data-orig-size="1650,950" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="2025.12.11 &amp;#8211;" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png?w=656" data-id="5534" src="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-5534" srcset="https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png?w=1024 1024w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png?w=150 150w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png?w=300 300w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png?w=768 768w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png?w=1440 1440w, https://therecouldhavebeensnakes.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2025.12.11-.png 1650w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
</figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Mike, blinded by some sorcery from the hairy chief’s axe, scrabbled around on the floor to wake his companions while Elixabete, having wrenched the charm-protecting shield from his grasp, took on the human-headed snake herself.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Unfortunately, Edward and Carbel were not so well protected and found themselves falling under the guardian’s charms and waking up the dormant hairy ones before wrestling the dwarf to the ground. Fortunately the newly awakened Koldobike was out of reach and able to pick off a few shots, and then slew Contithius with her spear when the serpentine guardian, seeing the hairy ones drop one by one, made a break for the grand set of double doors which led to the Snake-Armed Goddess’ sanctuary.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The charm lifted from the rest of the party and final hairy one. Ash his comrades recovered and grabbed Corinthius’ fancy-looking headpiece, Edward remembered the treasure trove that lay beyond those double doors and marched through. He firmly rejected the Snake-Armed Goddess’ proposal that he enter her service, and the enormous statue of her rumbled into life. The party fell back before its fierce blows, with both rescued prisoners walloped to death, and fled back up the stairs. The statue’s flailing fists struck the walls and ceiling, and Elixabete’s dwarven ears pricked up at the sounds of an almighty cave in.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bemoaning the fortune now buried beneath the rubble with a rather nasty sentry, the party dragged their battered, weary bodies back to the safety of Fourtowers Bridge.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">GM Notes</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>I need to get back in the habit of using the old campaign scrapbook, having reverted to scribbling session notes and prep in whichever pad of paper happens to be closest to hand. The two big fights found me referencing characters and monster stat blocks across four different sheets in three different pads, and it made the experience needlessly tricky. The campaign scrapbook had me putting in the effort up front by cutting up and pasting a load of dungeons to populate the map, and saved a lot more effort in the long run as I just had to pencil in notes in the copious amounts of white space I’d left by room keys. Ought to remember that lesson.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
